	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Design logo with photoshop and import it to game</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't know how to do it in Adobe® Photoshop® software, but in GNU Image Manipulation Program (GIMP), you can try this:<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Create a new image the same size as the image you want to convert. </li><li>Fill the image with one of the four colors in the desired pattern. </li><li>Using the pencil tool, draw at least one pixel of each of the three other colors. </li><li>Image &gt; Mode &gt; Indexed. </li><li>Colors &gt; Map &gt; Rearrange Colormap and drag the colors into the same order that they appear in the emulator's palette viewer. </li><li>Copy the image you want to convert and paste it into the new image's window. </li></ol>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


